# PROJECT.md — Mandatory Source of Truth

`PROJECT.md` at the repo root is the single authoritative document for this project.
**Read it before making any code change.**

## Before Writing Code

1. Read `PROJECT.md` — especially Section 4 (Architecture Rules), Section 6 (TODO), Section 7 (Bugs).
2. Never violate the Data Source Contract (Section 4.1) or Frontend/Backend Rules (4.2/4.3).

## After Completing Any Meaningful Work — Update PROJECT.md

| Section | What to update |
|---------|---------------|
| §5 Current Status | Flip ⚠️→✅ for completed items; add 🔄 for in-progress |
| §6 Active TODO | Remove completed items; add newly discovered items with priority |
| §7 Known Bugs | Add new bugs (status + file:line); remove fixed bugs |
| §8 Completed | Prepend `\| YYYY-MM-DD \| description \|` |
| §2/§10/§12/§13 | Update if infra, flows, file ownership, or env vars changed |

## Also Prepend a New Entry to PROGRESS.md

```
**Last updated**: YYYY-MM-DD — **Title:**
What changed and current state.
```

## Hard Rules (Non-Negotiable)

- No Supabase / Vercel / Netlify references in new code or docs
- No Motor API calls from `src/` — backend proxy only
- No `NgModule` in Angular
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after TS changes
- Run `node --check <file>` after backend JS changes
- Commit and push to GitHub after completing a task
- Push after every doc update — `PROJECT.md`, `PROGRESS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, or `documentation/` changes must be committed and pushed immediately
